Collaboration with @les83machines inspired by the latest drop from ALD. Dreaming up what the @los_york version would look like, and making some sexy typography inspired by the classics.

‘A Thought’ 2023
Acrylic on canvas
16x20 in

As an exercise on self observation and exploration, my therapist asked me to start doing visualizations of emotions. In the short time I have taken this on as a practice I realize that I rely on reduction and very graphic expressions to communicate what at times seems intangible. Through this practice I have also grown confidence and comfort in my art. As I am often victim of my own critical eye when it pertains my work, I have found this medium of creation to be freeing of the critic. Each piece - a full expression of a moment in time in my life - can not be put through the analytical lens. It is what was felt. Nothing more, nothing less.

This specific piece ‘A thought’ is a visualization of how on any given day, a thought can disrupt the systematic and structured way of thinking. Bringing a bit of color, texture and life, to an otherwise mundane and rigid existence.
